<item>
            <title>[WFCORE-22] Port version 1.6 of the management schema upstream.</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFCORE-22</link>
                <project id="12315422" key="WFCORE">WildFly Core</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;EAP will be introducing version 1.6 of the management schema, this needs porting upstream.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the same point the coding convention we have adopted has been based around a linear progression of the configuration schemas, when version 1.5 was ported this still worked as 1.5 contained a subset of the changes that went into 2.0.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.6 is going to be a special case as it will build on 1.5 so is already a subset of 2.0 but will also only contain a subset of changes that go into 3.0 - the risk however is our switch statements are built around dropping into a default block that is hit for all schema versions not explicitly listed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
